title: For Sale/Trade:  Minelab Explorer XS Metal detector
postcontent: This is one of the detectors that started the new rage in metal detecting. With it's ability to find a single silver dime at depths of 12 and even 14 inches, the Minelab Explorer XS became a must have detector for the serious metal detectorist. I have personally found Seated dimes at depths that I estimated to be 14 inches deep with one of these units. I purchased this detector off of Kenny Wray owner of Wray's Treasure Shop and a metal detectorist of over 40 years. He said that the owner of this detector only used it a few times and being an older fellow he thought that this unit was too complicated for him. The unit is in really nice,clean shape. Every function works on the detector and money back if it doesn't. This detector comes with standard battery pack, NiCad rechargeable battery pack with charger, car charger,Minelab headphones, coil stand, owner's manual, coil cover and fast start field guide. The only thing not here is the original box.  The LCD screen on this detector is flawless. The detector shows a little scuffing on the coil cover from normal use. I prefer to use the Minelab Explorer as a turn on and go machine. The only thing I change is the sensitivity setting. You simply push a button a few times to turn the sensitivity setting up for increased depth. You can also program this detector anyway you like. There are several books written on this subject. Please email any questions. Thanks! paid 1300.00

title: For Sale:  Muzzle Brake   Sound of Madness    S.O.M    $90 includes tax
postcontent:
The Rifenbark Armory engineering department has spent four months designing and prototyping the S.O.M. (Sound Of Madness) muzzle brake. We've always had specific goals in mind and would not accept anything less. 


Remove muzzle flip and lower felt recoil. 


Minimize grouping size due to less shot anticipation. 


Decrease shot split time by keeping your sights on target.

Engineering of the Rifenbark Armory Muzzle Brake: This is a ducted port muzzle brake that is calibrated to remove barrel rise and keep your sights on target.  The directional top ports are angled to provide compensation to the rising rotary force of muzzle climb. The 'valve cover' ports form a directional jet of gases as opposed to the typical plume you see in most muzzle brakes. Once muzzle rise on the S.O.M. (Sound of Madness) was controlled we began to remove felt recoil.  We accomplished this by incorporating characterized interruptions at specific locations in the side ports. These unify side to side forces as the bulk of the gases are dumped perpendicular to the axis of fire.  These features allow a precise amount of gas to release through the top ports (keeping the muzzle flat) while gases are re-directed out of the side baffles to prevent excessive felt recoil. postcontent:
Our # XM19469U

NO NYC. This listing is for THREE magazines; winning buyer, however, may take any number of additional magazines we have on hand at the same per-mag price and no extra shipping. Photos show genuine factory Smith & Wesson Magazines for the M&P .45 Smith & Wesson Pistols chambered in the venerable .45 ACP caliber. The M&P Pistols haven’t been in service long enough for us to get many of them or their magazines, but we do frequently trade with other dealers; and we trade and buy from police officers and our customers throughout the country. The photo specimens came from a 5 year tour of duty with the Distinguished Officers of the Agawam MA Police Department. Construction is serrated body matte stainless steel with black polymer floorplate and followers. These will work in any Smith & Wesson M&P 45 Pistol; these fit flush on service size variants but will protrude a bit on the Compact Variants. This magazine holds 10 rounds of .45 ACP caliber ammunition. These magazines themselves show the most significant of Smith & Wesson’s improvement upon Gaston Glock’s design; these magazines hold together, free-fall eject, and always lock the slide open just like they’re supposed to, something that cannot be said for Glock pistols and their magazines, admirable though they are. Surface wear on these comes more from carry in unlined leather magazine cases than from insertion and ejection. We estimate each one has been fired 300 times during annual qualification. We rate them as Very Good, but photos ought to suffice for our shoppers to judge finish grade for themselves. Replacement pricing on these in our area is in the $60 range, and they’re not easy to find at that. Our single mag onesy twosy price is $39.00. We’re offering the magazines in the photos, however, or their substantially identical mates from the same Department, in lots of 3 or more at $29 each. Own 3 for only $ 87.00. Not for sale to residents of New York City. Any magazine deliveries into New York City require written permission of the Police Commissioner, so we cannot ship magazines into any of the six boroughs or 176 some odd zip codes, per NYC Code 10-131.10. Civilian residents of New York State are legally enjoined from loading more than 7 rounds into any magazine. 

Grips, Magazines, slings, holsters, scopes, mounts, parts & most any small light items, entire accessory orders only $10.00 total shipping no matter how many a person buys. $10.00 for an entire order, Not $10.00 per item or anything of the sort. $20 Flat Fee on magazine orders to Alaska, Hawaii, or Puerto Rico, and gun parts to PR civilians must ship to an FFL. Mec Gar is the principal magazine supplier for Beretta, Browning, Kel-Tec, and Sig Arms, and wisely so. Their magazines are solid steel construction, superior springs, followers and floorplates. title: For Sale:  BRAVERMAN - STINGER "PEN-GUN"
location: INWOOD, WEST VIRGINIA 25428, Northern Virginia, Virginia
postcontent:
FOR SALE: BRAVERMAN - STINGER "PEN-GUN"

 This is a truly unique and collectable piece. Made in the '90s, this is a fully legal, ATF approved "Pen Gun". This gun was allowed by the ATF because it has to be converted to a "Gun Shape" in order to fire it.

 This is a one shot gun that even has a safety to prevent it from firing prematurely. Machined entirely from stainless steel bar-stock, this is a remarkably solid, well made and durable gun.

 It come complete with two barrels. One for .25 ACP and one for .17 HMR. The barrel includes the chamber for the round.
